    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - INSTALL - CLUTCH HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CLUTCH HOUSING</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Installation of the clutch housing is done in the horizontal position.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the clutch housing on the transmission case; align bolt holes with case holes (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026i7">Figure 187</hotlnk>). Install the bolts. Tighten to 145 to 155 ft-lbs. (197 to
                210 N&#8226; m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026i8">Figure 188</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026i7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026i7" filename="../figg13/g13026i7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 187. Install Clutch Housing on Transmission Case</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f13026i8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026i8" filename="../figg13/g13026i8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 188. Install Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
